\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 37. G. protopycnotrichum} Ehrend. & Krendl, {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  68}: 270 (1974). Stolons absent. Stems usually 60-80 cm, glabrous or often hairy, erect, with few weak branches. Leaves (15-)20-30 × 3-5 mm, broadly lanceolate, rather thin. Inflorescence relatively lax, oblong, the branches rather short and ascending; pedicels slender, shorter than the diameter of the corolla. Corolla 3-5 mm in diameter. Anthers yellowish to light brown. 2n = 22.{\i  Open and dry scrub and woods. • S.E.part of Balkan peninsula.} Bu Gr Ju.
