\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b 41-49}). {\b G. lucidum} group. Green or glaucous and pruinose; stock with or without stolons. Stems 15-70 cm, ascending or erect, glabrous or with short papillae or somewhat long hairs. Leaves 5-30 × 0·5-2 mm, mostly remaining green when dry, linear-oblanceolate to acicular, straight, with revolute or flat, scabrid or smooth margin. Inflorescence usually oblong to ovoid, with numerous internodes. Corolla often white, sometimes yellowish, rarely greenish or reddish, rotate and flat; lobes patent. Anthers usually light brownish when dry.
